29/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Friday (27 May) there would be no tolerance for corruption in the judicial sector. 
During a ceremony marking the 10th anniversary of Thessaloniki National School of Judges, Karamanlis stressed that Greek authorities are working to ensure that corruption is rooted out and that the Greek judicial system enjoys a reputation for professionalism. 
(ANA, MPA - 28/05/05)
